# Styling (Tailwind)

## Tokens, not ad-hoc colors

- Use **semantic utilities** tied to `src/index.css` `@theme` / CSS variables: `bg-background`, `text-foreground`, `text-muted-foreground`, `border-border`, `bg-card`, accents, **status** colors (`text-status-ok`, `text-status-warn`, `text-status-critical`, etc.).
- Avoid raw hex/rgb in class strings unless adding a new token in `index.css` first.

## Dark mode

- Use the **`dark:`** variant; the app drives theme via class **`dark`** on `<html>` (see theme rules). Do not rely only on `prefers-color-scheme` in components.

## Layout and density

- Prefer **flex/grid** + `gap-*`, responsive breakpoints (`sm:`, `lg:`), and `max-w-*` for readable line length on operator-facing copy.
- Interactive elements need visible **focus** styles (`focus-visible:ring-*`, `focus:outline-none` paired with ring).

## What not to do

- No `src/App.css`-style global component sheets; no styled-components unless the team explicitly changes stack.
- Do not strip `aria-*` or headings to “save space” — this is an operator dashboard.
